      "availableNightsFilter": {
        "name": "filter",
        "in": "query",
        "required": false,
        "description": "\"A filter query string narrows search results and supports the combination of logical and comparison operators. The filter adheres to the pattern filter='field' comparisonType 'value'.\"\n\nThese are the comparison types that can be used in filter expressions:\n* equal: eq\n* less or equal: le\n* greater or equal: ge\n* greater than: gt\n* less than: lt\n\nThe following fields are filterable:\n* attendeeType.codes (eq)\n* attendeeType.id (eq)\n* roomType.id (eq)\n* date (eq|le|ge|lt|gt)\n\nLimits for the number of fields that can be passed in a filter: 36\n\nThe following operators are available:\n* and\n* or\n",
        "schema": {
          "type": "string",
          "example": "attendeeType.codes eq 'PEWATT0524317' and (date ge '2023-01-12' and date le '2023-01-15')"
        }
      },
      "badgeId": {
        "in": "path",
